Deal.

77
00:04:06,590 --> 00:04:09,260
♪My wish is simple♪

78
00:04:09,260 --> 00:04:11,890
♪I want you to be with me forever♪

79
00:04:11,890 --> 00:04:13,570
♪Forgetting time♪

80
00:04:13,580 --> 00:04:14,500
Here it comes.

81
00:04:16,660 --> 00:04:17,660
Two spoonfuls.

82
00:04:17,930 --> 00:04:20,520
♪Not spinning in circles
within the rules♪

83
00:04:20,520 --> 00:04:22,970
♪I firmly chose what I love most♪

84
00:04:23,340 --> 00:04:24,180
Smells good.

85
00:04:25,180 --> 00:04:28,460
♪True to myself♪

86
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:38,540
I made it.

87
00:04:38,540 --> 00:04:40,420
I'll teach you
how to grow these scallions.

88
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:41,980
And cilantro.

89
00:04:43,220 --> 00:04:44,660
These two are the soul of it.

90
00:04:44,660 --> 00:04:46,380
It can grow easily right at home.

91
00:04:46,450 --> 00:04:51,510
♪Free and true to myself♪

92
00:04:57,540 --> 00:04:59,340
Thanks for taking care of me
all this time.

93
00:04:59,660 --> 00:05:00,500
Don't mention it.

94
00:05:05,460 --> 00:05:09,300
(One month later)

95
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:10,140
(Jiang Fang,)

96
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:12,860
(as expected, you didn't show up.)

97
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:15,420
(I thought maybe after that match,)

98
00:05:15,700 --> 00:05:17,300
(a miracle might happen.)

99
00:05:18,740 --> 00:05:20,060
(Seems I was overthinking.)

100
00:05:22,020 --> 00:05:23,900
(Maybe you're no longer in Jaya.)

101
00:05:24,180 --> 00:05:25,900
(Maybe you never planned
to see me again.)

102
00:05:26,740 --> 00:05:27,940
(Maybe I shouldn't)

103
00:05:28,660 --> 00:05:30,500
(have held such unrealistic hopes
for you.)

104
00:05:33,620 --> 00:05:34,710
(I've paid off your debt,)

105
00:05:35,580 --> 00:05:37,100
(but my life has to go on.)

106
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:39,160
(I have to live well)

107
00:05:39,170 --> 00:05:40,460
(to support Li Zan's education.)

108
00:05:40,460 --> 00:05:42,500
We're a traditional
Cantonese restaurant.

109
00:05:42,700 --> 00:05:43,660
With your northern

110
00:05:43,660 --> 00:05:45,260
cooking habits,

111
00:05:45,260 --> 00:05:46,440
you're not quite a fit for us.

112
00:05:46,740 --> 00:05:47,580
(Jiang Fang,)

113
00:05:48,860 --> 00:05:50,260
(I'm planning to become a chef.)

114
00:05:51,580 --> 00:05:53,380
This guy was recommended by Uncle Lin.

115
00:05:53,740 --> 00:05:55,700
(When you're finally willing to see me,)

116
00:05:55,940 --> 00:05:57,620
(let's have a cook-off.)

117
00:05:58,580 --> 00:05:59,420
Chop it.

118
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:01,340
(However...)

119
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:03,660
(Well.)

120
00:06:05,620 --> 00:06:08,900
(Finding a job is really hard.)

121
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:21,590
Miss,

122
00:06:21,620 --> 00:06:23,740
do you have any beef or pork belly?

123
00:06:23,740 --> 00:06:24,580
Sir,

124
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:28,940
the round steak today

125
00:06:28,940 --> 00:06:30,020
is really nice.

126
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:31,340
What?

127
00:06:31,660 --> 00:06:32,780
Only an animal's head?

128
00:06:34,820 --> 00:06:37,100
It means animal's neck.

129
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:38,260
This side is a chuck steak.

130
00:06:38,260 --> 00:06:39,740
This side is a round steak.

131
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:40,980
What round steak?

132
00:06:40,980 --> 00:06:43,460
Blade steak? What's that?

133
00:06:43,460 --> 00:06:45,060
If you're gonna stir-fry,

134
00:06:45,220 --> 00:06:46,780
use the big round steak.

135
00:06:46,780 --> 00:06:48,780
Great with dipping sauce.

136
00:06:49,060 --> 00:06:50,620
It's wrong, Miss.

137
00:06:51,140 --> 00:06:53,140
I don't want any of this.

138
00:06:53,460 --> 00:06:55,020
Sir, sir.

139
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:57,180
I've got beef.

140
00:06:57,420 --> 00:06:58,740
Come on, sir.

141
00:06:58,740 --> 00:07:00,420
You guys are so strict.

142
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:02,160
Do I need to pass a test
to buy beef here?

143
00:07:02,580 --> 00:07:03,540
That's not true.

144
00:07:03,540 --> 00:07:05,540
The new helper doesn't know.

145
00:07:05,850 --> 00:07:07,420
Here, I'll throw in an extra piece.

146
00:07:08,020 --> 00:07:10,380
This one's great for making soup.

147
00:07:10,740 --> 00:07:13,860
Soup? This one's perfect for soup.

148
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:15,380
I won't bother you anymore.

149
00:07:15,380 --> 00:07:17,460
I'll go check another place.

150
00:07:17,460 --> 00:07:18,780
Thanks. Take care.

151
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:20,060
Maybe next time.

152
00:07:22,060 --> 00:07:23,140
Sorry, boss.

153
00:07:24,300 --> 00:07:25,560
Boss, when can I start learning

154
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:27,640
how to select and cut meat
from the master?

155
00:07:29,180 --> 00:07:30,020
You've only been here

156
00:07:30,140 --> 00:07:31,980
for a dozen days.

157
00:07:31,980 --> 00:07:33,860
Learn from me first.

158
00:07:34,580 --> 00:07:35,420
What's the rush?

159
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:48,340
Ma'am.

160
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:49,380
I...

161
00:07:49,380 --> 00:07:50,660
I want this pork.

162
00:07:51,260 --> 00:07:53,220
Ma'am, how are you cutting it?

163
00:07:53,220 --> 00:07:54,300
I'll help you pick.

164
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:56,260
I'm using it for soup.

165
00:07:56,260 --> 00:07:57,140
For soup?

166
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:58,020
- Well.
- I want it.

167
00:07:58,020 --> 00:07:59,500
These aren't suitable for soup.

168
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:00,940
They're better for stir-frying.

169
00:08:00,940 --> 00:08:02,500
I'll cut you some different ones.

170
00:08:02,940 --> 00:08:03,810
Stir-frying then.

171
00:08:03,820 --> 00:08:04,980
I'm stir-frying.

172
00:08:06,220 --> 00:08:07,180
I want them all.

173
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:09,500
All four.

174
00:08:09,580 --> 00:08:10,460
One, two, three, four.

175
00:08:10,460 --> 00:08:11,600
- All of them.
- Pack them up.

176
00:08:12,660 --> 00:08:14,220
I'll help you pick two better ones.

177
00:08:14,220 --> 00:08:15,060
No need.

178
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:17,740
I like this girl's pork.

179
00:08:19,020 --> 00:08:19,860
Alright, alright.

180
00:08:20,140 --> 00:08:21,060
Okay, okay.

181
00:08:23,580 --> 00:08:24,980
Thank you.

182
00:08:37,300 --> 00:08:38,140
How much?

183
00:08:38,780 --> 00:08:39,620
300.

184
00:08:40,260 --> 00:08:42,140
200 is fine. How is it 300?

185
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:45,500
I'm not coming tomorrow.

186
00:08:46,140 --> 00:08:47,500
My granddaughter is on vacation.

187
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:48,980
It's alright. Just come.

188
00:08:48,980 --> 00:08:51,500
Here, take two bags of meat.

189
00:08:52,020 --> 00:08:53,860
Bye-bye, see you tomorrow.

190
00:09:49,860 --> 00:09:53,510
(Animal feet, aminal head,
animal neck, front leg)

191
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:57,790
(Front rib, pork shoulder, belly,
tenderloin, hind leg)

192
00:09:57,810 --> 00:10:00,540
(Ham, rump, top of rump)

193
00:10:36,580 --> 00:10:37,780
Li Zan, what are you doing?

194
00:10:38,420 --> 00:10:39,620
Why are you here?

195
00:10:39,820 --> 00:10:41,260
Ms. He called me again today,

196
00:10:41,260 --> 00:10:43,200
saying you skipped
half your classes this week.

197
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:45,540
I'm about to turn 18.

198
00:10:45,540 --> 00:10:47,020
I might as well go to work.

199
00:10:47,300 --> 00:10:49,780
Why are you so shortsighted?

200
00:10:49,780 --> 00:10:51,260
Even after this is all over,

201
00:10:51,260 --> 00:10:52,860
I'm not going to leave you behind.

202
00:10:53,380 --> 00:10:54,900
I'll support you through college.

203
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:56,180
So, stop worrying

204
00:10:56,180 --> 00:10:57,420
about this kind of thing, okay?

205
00:10:58,220 --> 00:10:59,980
The most educated person I've met

206
00:10:59,980 --> 00:11:00,820
was my dad.

207
00:11:01,620 --> 00:11:03,220
The least educated

208
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:04,420
is Luo Zheng.

209
00:11:04,740 --> 00:11:05,580
Who?

210
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:08,340
Luo Zheng. Mr. Luo.

211
00:11:08,780 --> 00:11:10,140
If I had collected debts

212
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:11,980
with those debt collectors

213
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,380
back then,

214
00:11:13,380 --> 00:11:15,100
would I have been rich by now?

215
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:16,300
You're a smart kid.

216
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:17,540
But I just don't get

217
00:11:17,540 --> 00:11:18,640
how your brain works.

218
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:20,000
Other people drop out to do that

219
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,780
because they don't have
the brains to study.

220
00:11:21,820 --> 00:11:22,760
You're a top student

221
00:11:22,860 --> 00:11:24,980
obsessed with living like a dropout.

222
00:11:24,980 --> 00:11:25,820
Why?

223
00:11:26,660 --> 00:11:27,500
My dad

224
00:11:27,900 --> 00:11:29,820
always cared a lot about my studies.

225
00:11:30,380 --> 00:11:31,740
The worst I ever did

226
00:11:31,740 --> 00:11:33,100
was the year I got chickenpox,

227
00:11:33,660 --> 00:11:36,020
and I still came third
in the whole grade.

228
00:11:36,020 --> 00:11:37,340
Listen, I would've loved it

229
00:11:37,340 --> 00:11:38,820
if someone cared about my studies.

230
00:11:38,820 --> 00:11:41,980
Sis, with the way your brain works,

231
00:11:42,980 --> 00:11:45,120
someone watching over you
wouldn't have helped much.

232
00:11:45,980 --> 00:11:47,060
When I was five,

233
00:11:47,300 --> 00:11:49,500
my mom asked my dad to buy a house.

234
00:11:50,300 --> 00:11:51,360
He didn't have the money.

235
00:11:52,260 --> 00:11:53,180
They fought,

236
00:11:54,060 --> 00:11:56,620
and my mom died of a heart attack.

237
00:11:57,180 --> 00:11:58,620
After that, my dad

238
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:00,060
never made any money in his life.

239
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:02,140
The year he died of cancer,

240
00:12:02,820 --> 00:12:04,460
I got first place in the whole city.

241
00:12:05,020 --> 00:12:06,060
What good did that do?

242
00:12:06,980 --> 00:12:08,380
What kind of logic is that?

243
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:11,660
If my dad had money

244
00:12:12,980 --> 00:12:14,100
and bought two apartments,

245
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:15,540
one for weekdays

246
00:12:15,540 --> 00:12:16,780
and one

247
00:12:17,140 --> 00:12:18,740
for weekends,

248
00:12:20,830 --> 00:12:22,460
my mom wouldn't have gotten mad.

249
00:12:23,740 --> 00:12:24,900
Then she wouldn't have

250
00:12:24,900 --> 00:12:26,220
had a heart attack and died.

251
00:12:28,020 --> 00:12:29,060
If we had enough money

252
00:12:29,780 --> 00:12:30,780
when my dad had cancer,

253
00:12:32,140 --> 00:12:33,360
we could've put him in the ICU

254
00:12:33,860 --> 00:12:35,100
and hired foreign specialists,

255
00:12:36,220 --> 00:12:37,820
and he might've lived another ten years.

256
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:41,820
But we didn't, so we were helpless.

257
00:12:47,820 --> 00:12:49,380
Money does solve a lot of problems,

258
00:12:51,860 --> 00:12:53,580
but it causes a lot too.

259
00:13:00,700 --> 00:13:03,140
Look at your face. It's filthy.

260
00:13:11,660 --> 00:13:12,900
It doesn't add up.

261
00:13:15,060 --> 00:13:15,900
Hold on.

262
00:13:16,940 --> 00:13:18,260
Did I miss something?

263
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:26,220
Five, six,

264
00:13:26,220 --> 00:13:27,060
seven, eight.

265
00:13:27,060 --> 00:13:27,900
That's right.

266
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:31,180
Without education,

267
00:13:31,180 --> 00:13:32,340
I can't even count money.

268
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:39,300
It's that room from earlier.

269
00:13:41,620 --> 00:13:42,460
Keep your voice down.

270
00:13:42,740 --> 00:13:43,900
Someone might hear.

271
00:13:46,980 --> 00:13:48,300
They paid,

272
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:49,420
so we have to meet

273
00:13:49,420 --> 00:13:50,740
their requirements.

274
00:13:52,420 --> 00:13:53,780
You knock on the door later.

275
00:13:54,420 --> 00:13:55,260
I'll hide first.

276
00:13:55,780 --> 00:13:56,620
OK.

277
00:14:11,940 --> 00:14:14,380
Weren't you supposed
to stall Jiang Fang?

278
00:14:15,340 --> 00:14:16,820
I stalled her for so long.

279
00:14:17,100 --> 00:14:18,460
I was more anxious than you.

280
00:14:19,260 --> 00:14:21,260
- Anyway...
- Do you not need her anymore?

281
00:14:26,540 --> 00:14:27,740
13,000. Thanks.

282
00:14:29,060 --> 00:14:30,460
She can't use this phone anyway.

283
00:14:30,460 --> 00:14:33,140
What's the point of my
spending that money?

284
00:14:34,180 --> 00:14:35,100
10,000, okay?

285
00:14:35,300 --> 00:14:36,140
No.

286
00:14:36,700 --> 00:14:38,140
